commit.message:
Fix EnumSupportSerializerMixin for non-editable fields

While DRF would regularly emit a ChoiceField for an enum field,
it emits a read-only CharField or IntegerField for a non-editable field instead.

Based on ADR-007's solution in #90.

Fixes #90
Warn when some values of an enum won't fit in the backing database field

Support Python 3.8 (#108)

* Test under Python 3.8

* Document Python 3.8 support

* Fix tox env arguments
Fix usages of force_text and ugettext_lazy to squelch Django 3.0 warnings
Drop support for EOL Django versions 1.8 and 1.10

Drop Python 3.4 support (EOL March 2019)

See https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0429/#release-schedule
See e.g. https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/py27-py34-deprecation.html
Add DRF related section to README
Add Django 2.1 and Django 2.2 to supported versions
Fix minor spelling mistake in README
Finagle tox.ini to make tests pass again

Remove test bits from setup.py

See https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/5534
